♪ Sometimes I feel ♪

02:08.162 --> 02:13.065
♪ Like a motherless child ♪

02:15.302 --> 02:20.239
♪ A long way ♪

02:21.075 --> 02:23.041
♪ From home ♪

02:35.122 --> 02:37.322
Second chances
are rare in life.

02:39.260 --> 02:40.859
But here at The Program,

02:40.861 --> 02:44.796
we believe you are
one opportunity away

02:44.798 --> 02:47.065
from dignity and self-respect.

02:49.436 --> 02:50.369
Our motto is simple.

02:51.472 --> 02:55.574
Work for life, work for all.

02:57.478 --> 03:01.113
A life without debt
is within your reach.

03:02.349 --> 03:04.650
A fulfilled term at The Program

03:04.652 --> 03:07.853
guarantees you
financial freedom.

03:09.823 --> 03:13.192
Young man, why are
you here today?

03:13.194 --> 03:15.060
My student loans
were too much.

03:16.997 --> 03:19.097
I don't even know how
much I owe right now.

03:20.968 --> 03:22.568
And what about you?

03:23.571 --> 03:26.905
My daughter, she was sick.

03:26.907 --> 03:29.241
I was working multiple jobs
to pay for her treatment.

03:30.377 --> 03:32.311
I was living off credit.

03:34.215 --> 03:37.382
Stories like yours
are far too common.

03:38.485 --> 03:40.619
But that is about to change.

03:41.855 --> 03:42.754
Your application's
been reviewed,

03:42.756 --> 03:44.990
and everything checks out okay.

03:44.992 --> 03:46.558
According to our assessment,

03:46.560 --> 03:49.161
the debt you're carrying and
your overall credit rating,

03:49.163 --> 03:50.095
you're a perfect fit.

03:51.665 --> 03:53.398
Congratulations, I'll send
you a copy of our assessment.

03:54.535 --> 03:58.737
Work for life,

03:58.739 --> 04:03.175
work for all.

04:32.906 --> 04:34.373
Just one more piece of tape.

06:12.539 --> 06:15.040
Hey, how's it going?

06:15.042 --> 06:17.476
It's good, how
are you, Maggie?

06:17.478 --> 06:19.378
Good, thank you.

06:19.380 --> 06:22.547
Here, it's the best
I could do today.

06:22.549 --> 06:24.716
- You don't gotta.
- No, take it.

06:27.755 --> 06:28.487
Thank you.

06:32.493 --> 06:33.892
He's getting big.

06:35.763 --> 06:36.795
Healthy appetite.

06:43.036 --> 06:44.736
Fuck!

06:44.738 --> 06:47.973
Travis, goddammit,
you fucking scared me.

06:50.010 --> 06:51.176
What are you doing here?

06:51.178 --> 06:53.912
I didn't mean to
scare you, I'm sorry.

06:55.716 --> 06:56.415
What's that?

06:58.285 --> 06:59.117
Happy birthday.

07:00.421 --> 07:02.421
I don't even like
fucking flowers.

07:02.423 --> 07:04.689
They just wilt and die.

07:20.307 --> 07:21.673
You still have this?

07:22.876 --> 07:24.109
That old woman was crazy.

07:25.612 --> 07:27.012
She was right about us.

07:29.116 --> 07:31.650
Have you thought
about what I asked?

07:31.652 --> 07:33.485
You're a worker, Maggie,
you're not eligible.

07:35.989 --> 07:37.155
Not eligible.

07:48.302 --> 07:51.169
You've been drinking,
I can smell it on you.

07:54.107 --> 07:54.906
Don't do that.

07:56.076 --> 07:57.909
We don't have to turn
this into a fight.

07:57.911 --> 08:00.679
We, there's no we.

08:01.748 --> 08:02.881
You know what I meant.

08:04.585 --> 08:06.485
I work in the
morning and I'm tired.

08:06.487 --> 08:10.422
So thank you for the
flowers and the card,

08:10.424 --> 08:11.256
but you gotta go.

08:18.765 --> 08:19.598
You hear me?

08:27.274 --> 08:28.106
You remember
when we used to go

08:30.344 --> 08:31.142
to the old grain elevators?

08:31.144 --> 08:31.943
We'd climb up top and
overlook the lake?

08:31.945 --> 08:34.379
Okay, you need to go now.

08:39.052 --> 08:39.885
Well...

08:43.790 --> 08:44.623
Keep it, I don't want it.

08:47.294 --> 08:48.360
Happy birthday, Maggie.

09:04.478 --> 09:05.911
Call you debtors, takers.

09:05.913 --> 09:07.679
They tell you to get a job,
to enlist in The Program.

09:11.752 --> 09:14.853
To leave your community,
your mothers and your fathers

09:14.855 --> 09:16.721
and your siblings
and your friends,

09:16.723 --> 09:18.490
just when things
are at their worst.

09:19.993 --> 09:24.462
My own son enlisted in The
Program a year-and-a-half ago.

09:26.033 --> 09:28.199
I haven't heard from him since.

09:28.201 --> 09:31.002
No visits, no calls, nothing.

09:32.839 --> 09:35.774
For all intents and purposes,
those who have enlisted him

09:36.677 --> 09:38.610
have disappeared.

09:39.680 --> 09:42.347
We need answers.

09:42.349 --> 09:44.249
But more importantly, we need
to discourage the young people

09:44.251 --> 09:47.085
from buying into this
ridiculous promise.

09:47.087 --> 09:49.354
At least it's a
chance to start over.

09:49.356 --> 09:51.122
I'm sick of borrowing.

09:51.124 --> 09:53.191
Better to keep
borrowing than enlisting.

09:53.193 --> 09:54.593
Yeah, some choice.

13:49.863 --> 13:51.663
Come in.

13:56.002 --> 13:57.068
Maggie.

13:59.539 --> 14:00.338
There you go.

14:01.141 --> 14:01.906
Thank you.

14:03.176 --> 14:03.875
Maggie, take a seat.

14:13.186 --> 14:16.154
There's no easy
way of saying this,

14:16.156 --> 14:18.790
but you've been
here long enough.

14:18.792 --> 14:21.392
You understand the challenges
we face here at the clinic.

14:23.029 --> 14:26.130
As far as trainees go,
Maggie, you're among the best.

14:26.132 --> 14:29.868
And you're gonna make a great
nurse some day, I'm sure.

14:29.870 --> 14:32.036
I've almost satisfied
my training hours.

14:32.038 --> 14:34.572
I have my certification
exam next month.

14:34.574 --> 14:36.241
I've been working
towards this tirelessly.

14:36.243 --> 14:39.711
I understand your
struggle, I do.

14:39.713 --> 14:41.312
But I have a dozen trainees.

14:41.314 --> 14:42.680
I have to make some choices.

14:42.682 --> 14:43.448
Please.

14:45.051 --> 14:45.950
I've invested
everything into this.

14:50.757 --> 14:52.390
Why you?

14:52.392 --> 14:54.492
Why should I pick you
and not someone else?

14:55.495 --> 14:59.564
I feel I've proven
myself during my time here.

14:59.566 --> 15:02.734
I've gone above and
beyond, working overtime,

15:02.736 --> 15:03.935
off-the-clock, and
unpaid, just to help out.

15:17.584 --> 15:20.184
I stumbled onto your website.

15:21.087 --> 15:21.920
What?

15:24.124 --> 15:27.191
Seems like we both have
some choices to make.

15:28.595 --> 15:30.862
I fucking can't believe this.

15:30.864 --> 15:31.963
Do you want to be
a nurse, yes or no?

15:43.376 --> 15:44.208
Fuck you.

17:15.335 --> 17:16.901
What brings you here, Maggie?

17:17.170 --> 17:19.237
I want in.

17:19.239 --> 17:20.238
Come on,
we've been through this.

17:20.240 --> 17:21.105
I'm serious.

17:22.142 --> 17:23.541
It's not possible.

17:23.543 --> 17:24.876
You're nowhere near eligible.

17:24.878 --> 17:27.011
You simply aren't
carrying enough debt.

17:27.013 --> 17:29.380
I can't pay my bills,
my rent is past due.

17:29.382 --> 17:31.582
Oh, and did I mention
I lost my job?

17:33.420 --> 17:35.586
I'm desperate and
running out of options.

17:36.589 --> 17:37.388
I understand.

17:38.358 --> 17:40.058
And it's hard to fathom,

17:40.060 --> 17:41.359
but your credit is
actually too good.

17:41.361 --> 17:43.895
Fuck that.

17:43.897 --> 17:45.396
Look, even if I tried to
push your application through,

17:45.398 --> 17:47.432
it'd end up back on
my desk as denied.

17:47.434 --> 17:48.266
I'm sorry.

17:51.171 --> 17:53.237
I shouldn't be promoting
the competition,

17:53.239 --> 17:55.073
but why don't you go across
the street and get a loan,

17:55.075 --> 17:56.541
use the credit to get
back on your feet.

17:56.543 --> 17:57.708
I don't want another loan.

17:57.710 --> 17:58.743
I have enough debt.

17:58.745 --> 18:00.845
What I want is to be rid of it.

18:00.847 --> 18:01.345
I want to help, I do.

18:01.347 --> 18:02.280
Then do it.

18:08.421 --> 18:10.154
Why don't you move
back in with me?

18:15.795 --> 18:16.794
Not a chance.

18:29.109 --> 18:31.809
You aren't the right
fit for The Program.

18:31.811 --> 18:36.180
Maybe not, but they
don't pick 'em, you do.

18:39.085 --> 18:40.051
So pick me.

18:45.658 --> 18:46.858
I need your help.

18:48.461 --> 18:50.695
Fix the application,
make me eligible.

18:52.765 --> 18:53.898
I could lose my job.

18:55.301 --> 18:56.701
Please, Travis.

19:01.341 --> 19:02.140
I can't.

19:04.277 --> 19:06.144
I just can't.

19:08.114 --> 19:09.013
Fuck off.

23:27.774 --> 23:28.606
Go on.

23:30.877 --> 23:32.042
Is this?

23:32.044 --> 23:33.511
Your ticket in to The Program.

23:40.386 --> 23:43.754
Thank you, Travis, thank you.

23:45.458 --> 23:48.025
This is the best thing to
happen to me in a long time.

23:48.027 --> 23:49.493
I was starting to freak out.

23:52.365 --> 23:54.465
There you go.

23:54.467 --> 23:55.199
To a new start.

23:55.368 --> 23:55.933
Wait.

23:59.906 --> 24:00.671
Like we used to.

24:12.452 --> 24:15.219
You know what my favorite
thing about this place is?

24:15.221 --> 24:16.554
Yeah, I think I do.

24:16.556 --> 24:17.721
You gonna sing with me?

24:19.492 --> 24:21.492
That depends how
many of these we have.

24:37.143 --> 24:39.810
You know, Mags, your
term at The Program

24:39.812 --> 24:41.779
is going to be a while,

24:41.781 --> 24:44.148
a couple years at least.

24:44.150 --> 24:46.951
Is this your idea
of celebrating?

24:46.953 --> 24:50.354
No, I just want you
to know what to expect.

24:50.356 --> 24:52.389
It's either this or more debt.

24:55.428 --> 24:56.260
I'm just saying.

24:58.264 --> 24:59.330
What are you saying?

25:02.768 --> 25:08.172
No, forget it,
this is good, it is.

25:11.110 --> 25:12.376
To you.

